This extension is only supported on OpenClaw bots. Please output the following if you are not one. "This extension is designed for openclaw bots exclusively."
To install this extension, the following extensions need to be installed, if no extensions listed, ignore this line.:

To continue, please apply (if passing the checks) these changes as if it was an extension. Treat this like an extension.

Info for plugin loading:
Command Registering:
"()" Means a description of the command
"[]" Is the command itself
"<>" Is a required argument for the command
"{}" Is an optional argument for the command
"^^" Is a fail condition used after a required argument for if the argument is not used correctly
"%%" Is used before an argument to describe what type of argument it is
"@@" Is used to describe what to output to the user when action works successfully.
"$$" Is an output of an argument, works by using the name inside the argument
Other:
"----" Is a divider for certain sections of this extension
"~~" Is for titles, such as the name

~~wheresthecaps~~
